# rule.forbid.stdout-on-exit-errors

error messages with `process.exit(1|2)` must use `stderr` (console.error), not `stdout`.

## .why

- cli hooks show stderr separately; stdout may be hidden on non-zero exit
- unix convention: stderr for errors, stdout for output
- pipe safety: errors on stdout corrupt data stream

## .pattern

```ts
// good
console.error('blocked'); process.exit(2);

// bad
console.log('blocked'); process.exit(2);
```

## .enforcement

`console.log` followed by `process.exit(1|2)` = **BLOCKER**
